com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class SyncCustomResourcesRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.SyncCustomResourcesRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class SyncCustomResourcesRequest
extends SiperianRequest
    Update related custom resources. This request is used to create custom secure resources that can then be associated with Roles using Hub Console. A client application can then request security privileges for those resources. This allows management of all resources (Siperian and custom) using the Hub Console.

    The set must contain all custom resources. The operation will insert new ones and delete ones missing from the request set. All insertions and deletions from the Hub database will be in a single transaction.

    User making this request must have update privilege to the SiperianObjectType.SAM_RESOURCE_METADATA "METADATA" resource.

    Required Parameters:

    • setCustomResourceSetName(String)
    • setCustomResourceNames(Set)

    Usage Example: The following example inserts or updates one resource in a set, and deletes any others already existing in that set. 

    
 SyncCustomResourcesRequest request = new SyncCustomResourcesRequest();
 request.setCustomResourceSetName("Accounting Portal");
 Set customResources = new HashSet();
 customResources.add("Main Page:View Acct");
 request.setCustomResourceNames(customResources);
 SyncCustomResourcesResponse response = sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    SyncCustomResourcesResponse, Serialized Form

    API Pair: SyncCustomResourcesResponse

    API Group: Security

      • validate

        public void validate()
        Validate the information provided in the request. This method throws SipRuntimeException if name of the custom resource set or names of custom resources are not valid. It validates that the names are not null or empty, names don't contain any "|" or "." special characters, names do not have leading or trailing spaces and the UIDs generated from the names are not longer than 255 characters. That is the size of the DB column that is used to store the UIDs. This method is called by the Hub Server to validate the names. It can also be called by the client application to validate the names before sending the request to the Hub Server.

      • getUids

        public Set getUids()
        Transforms setCustomResourceNames(Set) into UIDs.

        For each name: SAM_CUSTOM_RESOURCE .makeUid (getCustomResourceSetName(), name)

        The UIDs have the format CUSTOM_RESOURCE.Set_Name|Resource_Name, for example: "CUSTOM_RESOURCE.Accounting|MainPage:ManageAcct"

        validate() should be called before calling this method to make sure that the UIDs are valid.

        Returns:
        Strings that are custom resources. The Set can be empty but never null.
        Throws:
        com.siperian.common.SipRuntimeException - if the length of the UID of the custom resource is longer than the limit.
